    "Subsequently, for any queried English word, we similarly utilise BERT to extract its word vector v ∈ ℝ 768.",
    "Finally, the cosine similarity between the queried word vector and each vector e i in E is then calculated using the formula:where ⋅ indicates the dot product, and ‖v‖, ‖e i ‖ are the norms of vectors v and e i, respectively.",
    "The word within the vocabulary exhibiting the highest similarity to the queried English word is ascertained by identifying the index i that maximises the similarity measure.",
    "Therefore, compared to a one-to-one dictionary, our search system permits queries of words beyond the dictionary, providing users with more effective results.",
    "Meanwhile, when the highest similarity score falls below a certain threshold (i.e., 0.5), the query result is deemed null, indicating that our dictionary does not yet contain a relevant word."
